<br>
You should decide before you start if you want to mainly (and I say *mainly* because you'll want the option of switching) go 1h and shield, or 2 hand. If you go the shield use mainly you'll want 10 in dex, con, cha to start with and if you go 2 handed you'll want 10 in qui, str, cha. <br>
<br>
When speccing don't neglect parry. If you were a troll with low dex then parry wouldn't be such a good idea, and if you were a kobold I'd say make use of the high dex with reasonable parry levels. If your planning to go 1hand/shield put more on parry then if you went 2 handed. Don't spend too much on parry though.<br>
<br>
But really you'll have flexibility so don't worry too much. <br>
<br>
(I play a norseman skald btw) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/umaximumstorage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MaximumStorage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 8:44:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=201.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Strengths of a Norseman Skald?</span><hr size=1> Norse get 2% slash 3% crush, 5% cold resist.<br>
<br>
Trolls get 2% thrust resist and something else I forget maybe energy?<br>
<br>
Kobald get 5% crush and 5% something else?<br>
<br>
I never played a dorf I don't know theirs.<br>
<br>
Just something else to consider which small resist bonus you want.<br>
<br>
I am norse, 10 dex 10 quick 10 charisma. THe last month I have been using 1h and shield just because my shield adds slash/thrust/con/dex and my 2h just seems to slow against anyone with evade or to interrupt casters even with a quickness of about 105 using 2h.<br>
<br>
Misanthrope<br>
